The Anatomy of a URL

Resources on the World Wide Web are accessed through a Uniform Resource Locator (URL). A URL is a highly specified address that identifies both the protocol and the exact location of a resource.

URL Components

Component	Example	Description
Scheme	http://	Identifies the protocol; ends with a colon and double slash (://).
User Info	admin:password@	Optional credentials for authentication, separated by a colon and ended with @.
Host	inlanefreight.com	Signifies the resource location (hostname or IP address).
Port	:80	Separated by a colon. Defaults to 80 (HTTP) or 443 (HTTPS) if omitted.
Path	/dashboard.php	Points to a specific file or folder. Defaults to index.html if empty.
Query String	?login=true	Starts with ?; contains parameters and values. Multiple items use &.
Fragment	#status	Processed client-side to locate specific sections within a resource.


