HTTP Transaction Structure

The HTTP Request

The first line of a request contains the Method, the Path, and the HTTP Version. Following this are headers—key-value pairs describing the request—and an optional request body containing data.

The HTTP Response

The first line contains the HTTP Version and the Status Code. Like requests, responses include headers and an optional body, which may contain HTML, JSON, or binary files (PDFs, images).

Common Status Codes

* 1xx (Informational): Request received, continuing process.
* 2xx (Success): The action was successfully received and accepted (e.g., 200 OK).
* 3xx (Redirection): Further action needed to complete the request (e.g., 302 Found).
* 4xx (Client Error): The request contains bad syntax or cannot be fulfilled (e.g., 403 Forbidden, 404 Not Found).
* 5xx (Server Error): The server failed to fulfill an apparently valid request (e.g., 500 Internal Server Error).


