HTTP Headers Analysis

Headers facilitate information exchange between client and server. They are categorized based on their role in the transaction.

Header Categories

Category	Purpose	Examples
General	Contextualize the message, not the content.	Date, Connection
Entity	Describe the content being transferred.	Content-Type, Content-Length, Content-Encoding
Request	Sent by the client to provide context.	Host, User-Agent, Referer, Cookie, Authorization
Response	Sent by the server to provide context.	Server, Set-Cookie, WWW-Authenticate
Security	Define rules and policies for the browser.	Content-Security-Policy, Strict-Transport-Security


