CRUD Operations and API Interaction

Representational State Transfer (REST) APIs typically follow CRUD principles to interact with database entities.

Operation	HTTP Method	Description
Create	POST	Adds new data to the database.
Read	GET	Retrieves an existing entity.
Update	PUT / PATCH	PUT replaces an entire entry; PATCH performs partial updates.
Delete	DELETE	Removes a specified entry from the database.

Data Formats and Authentication

* JSON Data: Modern APIs frequently use JSON for data transfer. Requests must specify Content-Type: application/json for the server to interpret the input correctly.
* Authentication Persistence: Successful login typically results in the server sending a Set-Cookie header (e.g., PHPSESSID). If the browser or tool includes this cookie in subsequent requests (via the Cookie header), the session remains authenticated without re-entering credentials.
* Basic Auth: Uses the Authorization header with a Basic prefix followed by a Base64-encoded string of username:password.
